# Dataset Overview

The project uses the Brazilian Olist Marketplace dataset, which contains information about:

* Customers
* Orders
* Sellers
* Products
* Payments
* Reviews
* Geolocation
* Product Categories
* Order Items

The data captures the complete lifecycle of an e-commerce order, from purchase to delivery and customer review.

---

# Phase 1 – Data Cleaning (Microsoft Excel)

Before importing the data into Power BI, the datasets were reviewed and cleaned.

Tasks performed:

* Verified column consistency
* Checked for missing values
* Removed duplicate records where necessary
* Standardized date and number formats
* Inspected data quality
* Validated datasets before analysis

---

# Phase 2 – Data Audit (SQL)

A SQL data audit was performed to better understand the dataset and validate data quality.

The audit included:

* Exploring database structure
* Understanding relationships between tables
* Validating primary and foreign keys
* Identifying missing values
* Detecting duplicate records
* Checking order status distribution
* Analyzing customer and seller activity
* Exploring payment methods
* Reviewing product categories
* Generating exploratory business insights

This phase provided confidence that the data was suitable for reporting and helped identify important business questions for the dashboard.

---

# Phase 3 – Data Transformation (Power Query)

Power Query was used to prepare the data for reporting.

Tasks included:

* Importing multiple CSV files
* Renaming columns
* Correcting data types
* Removing unnecessary columns
* Creating calculated columns where required
* Preparing data for star schema modeling

---

# Data Modeling

A Star Schema was implemented to improve report performance.

## Fact Table

* Fact_Orders

## Dimension Tables

* Customers
* Sellers
* Products
* Order Items
* Payments
* Reviews
* Calendar

Relationships were created between fact and dimension tables to support efficient filtering and DAX calculations.

---

# DAX Development

DAX measures were created to calculate dynamic business metrics throughout the report.

The measures include:

### Financial Metrics

* Total Revenue
* Gross Profit
* Profit Margin
* Average Order Value
* Freight Cost %

### Sales Metrics

* Total Orders
* Products Sold
* Revenue by Category
* Revenue by Seller
* Monthly Revenue
* Month-over-Month Growth

### Customer Metrics

* Total Customers
* Average Review Score
* Positive Reviews
* Negative Reviews
* Customer Rating Distribution

### Logistics Metrics

* Total Sellers
* Order Fulfillment Rate
* On-Time Delivery Percentage
* Average Delivery Time
* Delivery Delay Analysis

These measures respond dynamically to slicers, allowing users to explore the data interactively.

